85 State Street, east side, between Castleton Avenue and Noale Place, showing the West New Brighton sub-branch of the New York Public Library. The sub-branch moved to the above address from 848 Castleton Avenue in 1923. In 1932 the sub-branch became a branch of the New York Public Library and moved into new quarters at 976 Castleton Avenue.

1924

P. L. Sperr

Castleton Ave., north side (houses thereon), east from State Street to Broadway. The view is from State Street.

March 24, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

State Street, at the N.W. corner of Market Street, showing the St. Benedicta Roman Catholic Church. To the right of the church is the rector's residence, number 22 State Street.

August 7, 1930

P. L. Sperr
